Java Day 04

  Primitive Data Types

  declearing variable :

  dataType variableName = data;

  int i1=5;
  int i2;
  i2=10;


  int  i3, i4;
  i3=3;
  i4=4;

  int i5=5, i6=6;

  numerical primitives:

        double> float > long > int > short > byte


  primitives :

        int : for integers
        double : for decimals
        char  : for single character   ''   single quote
        boolean: true or false

  Non Primitive:
         String: squence of characters, String of text---- ""   double quote
              String name = "Ahmet";


              CTRL +ALT+ L    will reformat code -- kode düzenler.



